The paper focuses on the human perception of task delegation to artificial intelligence, which is a topic that falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses factors such as motivation, difficulty, risk, and trust, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The use of surveys to collect judgments and preferences also suggests a connection to social and information sciences (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's focus on predicting human preferences and attitudes towards automation aligns with the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
